<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../AOML/sky.xsl"?>
<!-- FILE        : sky-2005.xml
     AUTHOR      : (C) Copyright by Peter C. Chapin
     SUBJECT     : Sky condition observations for 2005
-->
<observation-set xmlns="http://vortex.cis.vtc.edu/xml/AOML_0.0"
  xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
  xsi:schemaLocation="http://vortex.cis.vtc.edu/xml/AOML_0.0 ../AOML/AOML.xsd">

  <location>
    <value>
      <lat-long-alt>+43.00-072.50+300</lat-long-alt>
    </value>
    <notes>
      <xhtml:p>Central Vermont, USA</xhtml:p>
    </notes>
  </location>
  <observer>Peter C. Chapin</observer>
  <notes>
    <xhtml:p>The temperature and humidity measurements shown here were all made with a La Crosse
      WS-7078SUF weather station.</xhtml:p>
  </notes>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT15M">
      <ISO>2005-01-02T22:45:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>

    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">0.1</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">88</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>The sky is covered with clouds and freezing rain is falling. The steps in
            front of the house are very slippery. It is also rather windy.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>

      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>The sky is unobservable.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>0</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT15M">
      <ISO>2005-01-08T21:20:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>

    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">-5.6</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">84</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>The ground is covered with several inches of snow that fell this afternoon.
            However, at this time the sky is mostly clear with only a few areas obscured by haze
            or high clouds.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>

      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>Good conditions exist over most of the sky. Deep sky observations would be very
          possible. In some directions the limiting magnitude is somewhat inferior.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>4</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT15M">
      <ISO>2005-01-12T22:00:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>

    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">-1.5</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">86</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>It is totally cloudly and lightly sleeting.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>

      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>The sky is unobservable.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>0</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LDT" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2005-04-08T22:30:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>

    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">2.8</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">68</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>Cool but not cold. Some clouds in the north and west but otherwise
          clear.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>

      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>Aside from the clouds, the conditions are good. There is no moon and the sky is
          dark. All object types are observable. The clouds are a bit pesky, however, and they
          do detract from an otherwise excellent evening.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>4</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LDT" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2005-04-12T21:15:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>

    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">1.7</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">50</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>Generally clear skies, but some thin clouds.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>

      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>Quite a few stars are visible across much of the sky. However, there is a layer
          of high, thin clouds that washs out the faint stars and causes the bright stars to
          appear fuzzy. These clouds are particularly noticable in the vicinity of the waxing
          cresent moon.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>3</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

</observation-set>
